<h2>JavaScript Array Sort Reverse</h2>

<p>The reverse() method reverses the elements in an array.</p>
<p>By combining sort() and reverse() you can sort an array in descending order.</p>
<p id="demo"></p>
<button onclick="myFunction()">Try it</button>
<p id="demo1"></p>
<p id="demo2"></p>
<script>
// Create and display an array:
var fruits = ["Banana", "Orange", "Apple", "Mango"];
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML ="The orinal array is:" +fruits;
function myFunction() {
// First sort the array
document.getElementById("demo1").innerHTML ="Sorting of array is:" + fruits.sort();
// Then reverse it:
document.getElementById("demo2").innerHTML = " Reverse of fruits array is:" + fruits.reverse();
}
</script>
